  { '@type': 'Question', name: 'How does passionflower reduce anxiety?', acceptedAnswer: { '@type': 'Answer', text: 'Passionflower (Passiflora incarnata) contains chrysin and other flavonoids that act as GABA-A receptor agonists, directly binding to and activating the brain\'s primary inhibitory receptor system. This increases GABAergic neurotransmission, reducing neural excitability and promoting calm. Additionally, passionflower inhibits monoamine oxidase (MAO), which slows the breakdown of serotonin and dopamine — neurotransmitters involved in mood regulation. A randomized controlled trial comparing passionflower to the benzodiazepine oxazepam found comparable anxiolytic effects for generalized anxiety disorder, with passionflower producing less job performance impairment. The European Medicines Agency classifies passionflower as a traditional herbal medicinal product for relief of mild symptoms of mental stress and to aid sleep.' } },
